The paper deals with image recognition, specifically recognizing multiple objects in images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed model is a deep recurrent neural network trained with reinforcement learning, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves attention mechanisms, which is a popular research area in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.CL, in that order.
